      • inOrderTraversal

        public java.util.ArrayList<T> inOrderTraversal()
        Traverses the tree "in order". This means, the left subtree of the node is traversed first. Then, the node itself is visited. Then, the the right subtree is traversed.

        The data in each node is added to an ArrayList as the node is processed. In other words, this ArrayList stores the order of visiting of the nodes in the tree

        Specified by:
        inOrderTraversal in interface AVLTreeInterface<T extends java.lang.Comparable<T>>
        Returns:
        An ArrayList that stores the "data" field in nodes visited

      • bfTraverse

        public java.util.ArrayList<T> bfTraverse()
        Visits all the nodes in a breadth first manner. As nodes are visited, "data" fields are added to an ArrayList.
        Specified by:
        bfTraverse in interface AVLTreeInterface<T extends java.lang.Comparable<T>>
        Returns:
        An ArrayList that stores the "data" field in nodes visited

      • areCousins

        public boolean areCousins​(T element1,
                          T element2)
        For two nodes, if their distances to the root is the same and their parents are not the same, they are said to be "cousins".

        Of course, if one of the parameters is not in the list, they cannot be cousins.

        Specified by:
        areCousins in interface AVLTreeInterface<T extends java.lang.Comparable<T>>
        Returns:
        true if elements in the parameter are cousins, false otherwise

      • balanceFactor

        public int balanceFactor​(T data)
        Returns the balance factor of the node that stores the data given as parameter BalanceFactor: height(leftSubtree) - height(rightSubtree)

        You may assume that there will be one and only one node whose balance factor is calculated
